Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer visited Colombia and met with President Ivan Duque, President-Elect Gustavo Petro, Vice President-Elect Francia Marquez, and other Colombian elected officials. During the visit, Mr. Finer expressed gratitude on behalf of President Biden for President Duque's partnership, specifically highlighting his efforts on climate change and regional migration. He also congratulated President-Elect Petro and Vice President-Elect Marquez, emphasizing the Biden-Harris Administration's commitment to a strong relationship based on equal partnership and the historical ties between the two countries. The discussions between Mr. Finer and the incoming administration covered various areas of common ground, such as combating climate change, promoting economic development in rural areas, and advancing the implementation of Colombia's 2016 peace accord. Both parties expressed their intention to continue engaging in the future.